message.content: "cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR". This paper focuses on using visual questions as a form of weak supervision for image datasets, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques used in visual question answering. Additionally, the paper explores data augmentation strategies (cs.IR) to improve performance on the VQA benchmark.
